ENTRY       EC 1.1.1.78                 Enzyme
NAME        methylglyoxal reductase (NADH);
            methylglyoxal reductase;
            D-lactaldehyde dehydrogenase;
            methylglyoxal reductase (NADH-dependent)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     (R)-lactaldehyde:NAD+ oxidoreductase
REACTION    (R)-lactaldehyde + NAD+ = methylglyoxal + NADH + H+ [RN:R02527]
ALL_REAC    R02527
SUBSTRATE   (R)-lactaldehyde [CPD:C00937];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003]
PRODUCT     methylglyoxal [CPD:C00546];
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     This mammalian enzyme differs from the yeast enzyme, EC 1.1.1.283, methylglyoxal reductase (NADPH-dependent), in preferring NADH over NADPH as reductant.
